A.2.4. Reproduction Reproduction occurs 20 days after zooplankton reaches its maximum weight Gmax. After the eggs are hatched, the number of adults decreases over the next 20 days. All biomass accumulated during the 20 days of gestation prior to hatching goes to eggs. All biomass goes to corpses after death (the corpses are counted as part of the detritus). The transition from juvenile to adult takes place when the Gmax is exceeded

