=

aD

(A.16)

where D is the biomass of the detritus material and a is the decay term (=0.01 d−1). The detritus biomass that is reminer-
alised is converted to ammonium. Other sources of ammo-
nium in the model are carnivorous grazing, mortality after reproduction 0.9na·(G − Gmax) and the basal zooplankton respiration rate (Eq. (A.10)).

